{"type":"message","id":"2969a2f9","parentId":"659a3b12","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:57:33.192Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_io4ojcv9wt6n_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 105700\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nCurrent status:\r\n- Phase 0 and 1 are complete\r\n- CFI analysis was just completed - found that 44.8% of frequency-invariants have CFI=0 (pure noise), only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7)\r\n- Next pending action: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that we need to:\r\n1. Implement CFI filtering to distinguish true causal anchors (CFI>0.7) from metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0)\r\n2. Run an experiment comparing CFI-weighted compression vs frequency baseline for next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe most logical next step is to implement a script or analysis that:\r\n1. Takes the CFI results\r\n2. Creates a CFI-weighted compression approach\r\n3. Compares it to frequency-only baseline\r\n4. Measures prediction quality\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action: implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment script.\r\n\r\nI'll create a new script that:\r\n1. Loads the CFI results from `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\r\n2. Applies CFI-weighted filtering to the invariants\r\n3. Compares prediction quality vs frequency baseline\r\n4. Outputs results\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending items, the most concrete next action is to implement the CFI filtering logic and set up the comparison experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script that:\r\n1. Processes the frequency invariants with CFI weights\r\n2. Compares prediction performance\r\n3. Generates results\r\n\r\nThis is concrete and advances the pending goal.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants are either noise (CFI=0) or weak signals (CFI<0.7). The next logical step is implementing CFI-weighted compression to test whether filtering by causal strength improves next-pulse prediction over frequency-only methods.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a Python script to implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment that compares prediction quality using CFI>0.7 threshold vs frequency-only baseline.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nCFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\nCompares next-pulse prediction using:\r\n  1. Frequency-only baseline (current method)\r\n  2. CFI-weighted filtering (CFI >= 0.7 = causal anchor)\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\n# Load CFI results\r\ncfi_results_path = Path(\"research/CFI_RESULTS.md\")\r\nwith open(cfi_results_path) as f:\r\n    content = f.read()\r\n\r\n# Extract CFI scores\r\ncfi_scores = {}\r\nfor match in re.finditer(r'\\|\\s*([\\w\\-\\.]+)\\s*\\|\\s*([\\d.]+)\\s*\\|', content):\r\n    node_name = match.group(1)\r\n    cfi = float(match.group(2))\r\n    cfi_scores[node_name] = cfi\r\n\r\n# Load frequency data\r\nfreq_results_path = Path(\"research/FREQUENCY_ANALYSIS.md\")\r\nwith open(freq_results_path) as f:\r\n    freq_content = f.read()\r\n\r\nfreq_scores = {}\r\nfor match in re.finditer(r'\\|\\s*([\\w\\-\\.]+)\\s*\\|\\s*(\\d+)\\s*\\|', freq_content):\r\n    node_name = match.group(1)\r\n    freq = int(match.group(2))\r\n    freq_scores[node_name] = freq\r\n\r\n# Strategy 1: Frequency-only (top 20 by frequency)\r\nfreq_baseline = sorted(freq_scores.items(), key=lambda x: -x[1])[:20]\r\n\r\n# Strategy 2: CFI-weighted (CFI >= 0.7)\r\ncfi_filtered = {k: v for k, v in cfi_scores.items() if v >= 0.7}\r\ncfi_ranked = sorted(cfi_filtered.items(), key=lambda x: -x[1])[:20]\r\n\r\n# Overlap analysis\r\nfreq_set = set(k for k, v in freq_baseline)\r\ncfi_set = set(k for k, v in cfi_ranked)\r\noverlap = freq_set & cfi_set\r\nonly_freq = freq_set - cfi_set\r\nonly_cfi = cfi_set - freq_set\r\n\r\nprint(\"=\" * 60)\r\nprint(\"CFI-WEIGHTED COMPRESSION EXPERIMENT RESULTS\")\r\nprint(\"=\" * 60)\r\nprint(f\"\\nFrequency Baseline (top 20 by frequency):\")\r\nprint(f\"  Count: {len(freq_baseline)}\")\r\nprint(f\"  Avg CFI of top freq nodes: {sum(cfi_scores.get(k, 0) for k, _ in freq_baseline) / len(freq_baseline):.3f}\")\r\n\r\nprint(f\"\\nCFI-Weighted (CFI >= 0.7):\")\r\nprint(f\"  Count: {len(cfi_ranked)}\")\r\nprint(f\"  Avg frequency of high-CFI nodes: {sum(freq_scores.get(k, 0) for k, _ in cfi_ranked) / max(len(cfi_ranked), 1):.1f}\")\r\n\r\nprint(f\"\\nOverlap Analysis:\")\r\nprint(f\"  Common to both: {len(overlap)} nodes ({100*len(overlap)/20:.1f}%)\")\r\nprint(f\"  Only in freq: {len(only_freq)} nodes\")\r\nprint(f\"  Only in CFI: {len(only_cfi)} nodes\")\r\n\r\nprint(f\"\\nKey Finding:\")\r\nif len(cfi_ranked) > 0:\r\n    high_cfi_low_freq = [k for k, _ in cfi_ranked if freq_scores.get(k, 0) < \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 10:57:26\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774364253190}}
